  "description": {
   "en": "\"The words that I've longed to hear for years, only to hear them from you, a man I've just met.\"\n\nActor Fujinaga (a sophomore in college) loves acting. But he has been failing auditions so often that he has lost confidence. It was then that he met Keito (a first-year college student) with congenital hearing loss.\nDespite this being Fujinaga's first experience with sign language, he was able to read the hand movements at a glance because he had been acting with more of a desire to \"convey\" the message than anyone else. He eventually decides to try sign language with gestures, which surprises Kate with his talent to see how Fujinaga expresses his emotions.\n\nUniversity student with hearing loss x unsuccessful actor. A heartwarming love story that connects hearts through sign language."
  },
